reviewText: Great home scary movie. Grab your popcorn and large soda!
Quality of picture is bad. i had to run it thru an upconverting program and reburn it to watch on the main tv.

I was expecting a horror film, but it's blandness reminded me of some ill-advised family drama.  I made it about until 30 minutes to the end, then I just didn't care what happened.  I did catch the last blip of the end and it was just pointless.  It isn't sure if it wants to be a ghost horror film or a psychiatric drama on Lifetime TV.  I hope the director hasn't made anything else, he's not up to par.

This is a lifetime movie I really enjoyed since I like ghost/haunting stories and would like to own it on DVD but saw it is currently unavailable on this site .If someone knows where I can get it please let me know.
